parameters: \N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... What's wrong, Segi? Did you come to see me? Huh?
\N<Zuuteruka>...
I wish to have an audience with Yuia.
I have no business.
ユイアとの面会を希望する
\N<Zuuteruka>...Let me see Lord Yuia.

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... A little test of the marital bonds, huh? Well,
fine. Enjoy your chat in the dark dungeon.
air08
air05
用事は無い
\N<Segi>...

\N<Zuuteruka>Don't glare at me like that. With that kind of look, I'm too
scared to even talk about important matters.

\N<Segi>...If you have time to joke around, why not just get on with
it? You have something to tell me, right...?

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... Yeah, it's an important matter. It's about whether
you can participate in the training soldiers' assembly as
Yuia's proxy or not.
\N<Segi>...

\N<Zuuteruka>I proposed to the main Ryuda troops to let you take the
stage at the training soldiers' assembly. Their response
finally arrived this morning.

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... To get straight to the point, the proposal was
accepted. But the main troops have set two conditions for
it.

\N<Zuuteruka>Accepting the conditions laid out by the main Ryuda troops
is the absolute requirement for you to participate in the
assembly as a proxy.
\N<Segi>Two absolute conditions...?

\N<Zuuteruka>Yeah, I've said it many times, but Yuia is a serious
criminal. Normally, he wouldn't have any complaints even if
he were to be hanged immediately.
\N<Segi>...

\N<Zuuteruka>Of course, that means he has no right to participate in the
training soldiers' assembly. But if you accept these
conditions, they're willing to let you participate as his
proxy.

\N<Segi>What exactly are those conditions...? Don't beat around the
bush, tell me. No matter what the conditions are, I will
accept them all for Lord Yuia and Riia's sake.
\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... Don't forget what you just said, alright?

\N<Zuuteruka>The condition imposed on you... It's simple. You have to
become a devout mistress for us Ryuda.
セギ_驚愕
\N<Segi>...Eh...?

\N<Zuuteruka>And as Ryuda's mistress, regardless of whether you win or
lose in the assembly battles, you must offer your body to
your opponent regardless of the outcome.
セギ_驚愕
\N<Segi>Wha...wha...!?

\N<Zuuteruka>Hey hey, didn't you hear me? In other words, as Ryuda's
mistress, you have to sleep with your opponent whether you
win or lose in the assembly.

\N<Segi>Don't joke with me!! There's no way I can agree to such a
thing!!

\N<Zuuteruka>Don't think about it too deeply. If your opponent is a man,
then it's just like being a male prostitute, a male
prostitute. Just think of it as buying a man for one night.
\N<Segi>Wha...!!??

\N<Zuuteruka>You... have you forgotten? When you volunteered to be Yuia's
proxy, what did you say to me?
white
...Alright. I'll do as you wish.
\N<Segi>Grr...!

\N<Zuuteruka>Moreover, according to the main troops, the purpose of this
measure is not only to boost the morale of the opponents but
also to alleviate their war-weariness.

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... In other words, if you win, you buy your opponent,
and if you lose, your opponent buys you. Is that easier to
understand? Either way, it's guaranteed to boost the
opponent's morale.

\N<Segi>Tha-that's ridiculous...! That means in the end I am... I
am!!

\N<Zuuteruka>Hey, Segi. You're not thinking you can stay beautiful and
pure and win through the training soldiers' assembly, are
you? If so, that's naive. It's not a stage where you can
stand with such half-hearted resolve.

\N<Zuuteruka>Fight with everything at stake. Even if you're violated and
defiled by beast-like men and end up pregnant with a
child... The question is whether you still want to save your
family.

\N<Zuuteruka>Do you have that resolve? If not, your husband will be
hanged. Your son will have to become a male prostitute for
some rich guy at his young age, or else he'll be sent
straight to the battlefield and off to the next world.
\N<Segi>Grr...! Such things should be done by me...!

\N<Zuuteruka>You won't allow it? Then accept the conditions. I'll prepare
a path for you to carve out that tragic future.
\N<Segi>...
\N<Zuuteruka>...

\N<Segi>...I understand... Fine. I'll accept those conditions...
right?

\N<Segi>But! In exchange for that, you must not tell Lord Yuia about
this...!

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe, I understand, I'll keep quiet about it. Well, that's
a wise choice. It's by sacrificing yourself that you can
protect what's important, hehehe.
\N<Segi>...

\N<Zuuteruka>With this, your opponent will surely be motivated. After
all, whether they win or lose, they get to sleep with you,
huh?

\N<Zuuteruka>It's perfect for dispelling any reluctance to fight. The
purpose of the training assembly is to recruit strong
soldiers. It's all good news, isn't it? Eh?
\N<Segi>...
\N<Zuuteruka>Now then, onto the second condition.

\N<Zuuteruka>Regardless of what you think, Yuia is a criminal. Moreover,
one deserving of death. Normally, there would be no reason
to keep him alive.
\N<Segi>...

\N<Zuuteruka>However, I'll let him live. By the authority vested in me as
the commander stationed in this town.

\N<Segi>...There's no need to emphasize that now. Should I express
my gratitude?
\N<Zuuteruka>That's necessary, but it's not enough.

\N<Zuuteruka>To pardon a serious offender and keep him alive, we need a
reason good enough to satisfy the main Ryuda forces.
\N<Segi>A reason to satisfy Ryuda...?

\N<Zuuteruka>Yes. To put it bluntly, we need something tangible... a
tribute to the forces.
\N<Segi>A tribute...? That's ridiculous...

\N<Zuuteruka>There's nothing ridiculous about it. It's only natural when
bending the rules. After all, greasing palms is most
effective in such situations.

\N<Zuuteruka>And... it goes without saying that if a person doesn't eat,
they die. There's no rule in Ryuda that says we have to feed
a death row prisoner.
\N<Segi>...

\N<Zuuteruka>But for Ryuda, that's the normal course of action. After
all, their custom is to carry out beheadings on the same day
they're decided.

\N<Zuuteruka>In other words... the cost of Yuia's food and maintenance,
which shouldn't even be necessary, must also be included in
the tribute.
\N<Zuuteruka>All told, it'll come to about 1000 MO in just a few days.
\N<Segi>1000 MO...! There's no way I have that kind of money...!

\N<Zuuteruka>If you don't have it, make it. It's simple. If you can't
come up with the money, Yuia will be executed immediately.
\N<Segi>That's... that's absurd...!

\N<Zuuteruka>I've said it before, but this is a concession. You need to
show your resolve.

\N<Zuuteruka>And that resolve must be something visible. That's the
visualization of resolve.
\N<Segi>...

\N<Zuuteruka>Listen up? I'll say it again, make the money. I don't care
how you do it.

\N<Zuuteruka>You can search the ruins or earn it through unspeakable
jobs. That will be the thread that ties your husband's life.

\N<Zuuteruka>Of course, I won't force you. If you believe you can save
your husband without getting hurt or dirty, that's fine too.

\N<Zuuteruka>Or perhaps you decide to literally see hell together with
your husband. Either way, whether your husband lives or dies
is up to you.
\N<Segi>...Understood. I will definitely prepare the money.
\N<Zuuteruka>That's right, that's the spirit. I'm looking forward to it.
\N<Segi>In exchange... I have a condition of my own.
\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... Are you in a position to make conditions?

\N<Segi>It's not a big condition. Allow Lord Yuia and me... to meet
freely.
\N<Zuuteruka>Oh...?
\N<Segi>It's only natural, right? I can't trust Ryuda or even you.

\N<Segi>No matter how much tribute money I prepare, there's still a
chance you could break your promise.
\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... Well, that's true.

\N<Segi>You talked about visualizing resolve, didn't you? Then you
should also make your side visible.

\N<Segi>That should be possible within your authority without having
to consult with the main Ryuda forces, right?
\N<Zuuteruka>...Understood. Very well.

\N<Zuuteruka>But remember this, don't you dare break your promise, okay?
If you do... your beloved husband and son will have nothing
but death.
\N<Segi>...

weather : 1 : 5 : 5 : 5 : 1 : Light_01C : 1
\N<Segi>The sun is already so high...

\N<Segi>It's frustrating, but Zuuteruka is right. I don't have the
luxury to waste time idly...
\N<Segi>...I must become stronger. For Riia, for Lord Yuia...
\C[1]【Information】\C[0]

From now until the start of the training assembly, you will
basically be able to act freely.
\C[1]【Information】\C[0]

Use the limited time before the training assembly starts
effectively. Train yourself within the ruins, acquire useful
items, and gather information about the enemy.
\C[1]【Information】\C[0]

In addition to growth items that can be obtained inside the
ruins, Segi's abilities will also grow by visiting her
imprisoned husband Yuia.
\C[1]【Information】\C[0]

Additionally, sleeping in your own bed at home will fully
restore your health, and one day will pass.
\C[1]【Information】\C[0]

Furthermore, items regarding the training assembly and other
rules can be checked at home, so please refer to them.

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... How does your first taste of battle feel?
\N<Segi>...

\N<Zuuteruka>Can't put it into words, huh? To think you betrayed your own
husband to save him.

\N<Zuuteruka>Right? How does it feel to be reminded of that? Makes you
want to run away from the despair in front of you, doesn't
it?

\N<Segi>Don't be ridiculous. I won't go anywhere, leaving Lord Yuia
and Riia behind.
\N<Segi>My heart... is not yet broken.

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe, such noble resolve. I was worried you might just run
away out of self-preservation, abandoning your husband and
son.

\N<Segi>Don't underestimate me. You should have understood my
determination long ago. There's no need for such suggestive
talk.

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... Well, that's true. Yuia is indeed a lucky man.
Even faced with the threat of death, his wife is here,
literally devoting herself to him.

\N<Segi>How many times must I tell you not to wag your unnecessary
tongue?

\N<Segi>...Speak up. You called me here because you have something
to discuss, right?

\N<Zuuteruka>Quick to the point. That's why I can keep Yuia alive. It's
precisely because you're willing to grind yourself down for
me...
\N<Segi>...

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... You understand, right? Becoming Lyuda's mistress
means nothing more than becoming my woman.
\N<Segi>...

\N<Zuuteruka>Literally forget about your husband and son, and become an
obedient mistress who spreads her legs for me.

\N<Segi>Stop joking. There's no way I would forget about Lord Yuia
or Riia even for a moment.

\N<Zuuteruka>I'm not joking at all. You conveyed your demands to me, and
in turn, I've conveyed mine to you.

\N<Zuuteruka>Either abandon your current self to save your husband, or
stick to your love for him and let the man himself die.

\N<Zuuteruka>The choice is yours. After all, there's no real need for me
to show any mercy to your family. The fact that you have a
choice is an exceptional act of mercy.
\N<Segi>...

\N<Zuuteruka>That being said... the love between a husband and wife is
important to you, isn't it? That's why I won't tell you to
spread your legs right here and now.

\N<Zuuteruka>Let's see... I'll give you four days. I'll wait four days
for you to firm up your resolve.

\N<Zuuteruka>If you refuse, then it means breaking the conditions for
participating in the military training. You know what will
happen to your husband and son then, right?

\N<Zuuteruka>In four days... you'll choose whether to become my mistress
and save your husband or let the man you love die. Ponder
that until then. Hehehe... Aren't I kind?
\N<Segi>...

\N<Zuuteruka>Don't glare at me like that. Can't you see I'm showing
mercy? Well, you must be tired today, right? After all
that's happened. Let's continue this conversation... another
time.
\N<Segi>Before that... let me see Lord Yuia.

\N<Zuuteruka>Oh? What's this? Planning to bid farewell to your beloved
husband? "I will belong to this man now~ So this is
goodbye~" or something like that?

\N<Segi>Haven't I told you not to wag your useless tongue? Just
hurry up and show me the way...
\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... Alright, alright, such a demanding woman.
B
